title: Dan Mullen celebrated Mississippi State's win by videobombing Dak Prescott on live TV
text:
Dan Mullen celebrated Mississippi State's win by videobombing Dak Prescott on live TV SB Nation 6 hrs ago Mark Sandritter Mississippi State quarterback Dak Prescott was going through a postgame interview on the SEC Network when all of a sudden some jokester decided to videobomb him.
AdChoices Â© Provided by SB Nation Wait ... that isn't any prankster, it's MSU head coach Dan Mullen! The Bulldogs improved to 6-2 with a resounding 42-16 win against Kentucky, and apparently Mullen was feeling very good about being bowl eligible. From wearing Yeezys to videobombing his own players on live TV, Dan Mullen is quickly becoming one of the most fun coaches in college football.
